'l'hat the Ode was not written at that time is still more certain. Augustus did not then occupy the whole horizon of politics. Horace was at Athens, and on the point ofjoining the army of Brutus. Franke places its composition in Rc. 29, when Augustus returned to Rome after the victory of Actium, and celebrated his threefold triumph (see v. 495. If Horace identifies sor a moment the ‘ scelus expianclum’ with the death of Caesar, his thoughts at least are not running on any cruel vengeance when he sees in the avenger the incarnation of ‘gentle Maia's son,’ the god of peaceful arts, of prudence and persuasion‚ of commerce and wealth.
